        <div id="faq" class="faq-area are_sections_faq py-120 caaft-ar-faq-wrap" aria-labelledby="ac-faq-heading"><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-lg-12"><div class="faq-right wow fadeInUp"><div class="site-heading text-center mb-3"><h2 id="ac-faq-heading" class="site-title my-3">Frequently Asked Questions:</h2></div></div></div><div class="frequent-question col-lg-10"><div class="accordion wow fadeInRight" id="accordionAdvisoryFaq">
            <div class="accordion-item"><p class="accordion-header" id="acFaqHeading1"><button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#acFaqCollapse1" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="acFaqCollapse1">01. What is the difference between a virtual CFO and a regular accountant?</button></p><div id="acFaqCollapse1" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="acFaqHeading1" data-bs-parent="#accordionAdvisoryFaq"><div class="accordion-body">An accountant records and reports what has happened. A virtual CFO uses those records to advise on what should happen next - managing cash flow, building financial models, advising on funding strategy, reviewing contracts, and sitting in on board or investor conversations. CAAFT's CFO service is built for businesses that have outgrown basic accounting but are not yet ready for a full-time finance head.</div></div></div>
            <div class="accordion-item"><p class="accordion-header" id="acFaqHeading2"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#acFaqCollapse2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="acFaqCollapse2">02. At what stage of business does a virtual CFO engagement make sense?</button></p><div id="acFaqCollapse2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="acFaqHeading2" data-bs-parent="#accordionAdvisoryFaq"><div class="accordion-body">Typically when your business is growing fast, raising funds, managing multiple revenue streams, or facing decisions that have significant financial consequences. If you find yourself making major financial decisions without a structured view of your numbers - or relying entirely on your accountant's year-end report - it is probably time.</div></div></div>
            <div class="accordion-item"><p class="accordion-header" id="acFaqHeading3"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#acFaqCollapse3" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="acFaqCollapse3">03. How is your Business Valuation different from an online valuation tool?</button></p><div id="acFaqCollapse3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="acFaqHeading3" data-bs-parent="#accordionAdvisoryFaq"><div class="accordion-body">Online tools apply generic multiples to surface-level numbers. CAAFT's valuations are methodology-driven - using DCF, comparable company analysis, or asset-based approaches depending on the purpose - with full documentation of assumptions, adjustments, and rationale. The result is a valuation that stands up to scrutiny from investors, acquirers, or courts.</div></div></div>
            <div class="accordion-item"><p class="accordion-header" id="acFaqHeading4"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#acFaqCollapse4" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="acFaqCollapse4">04. Can CAAFT prepare a feasibility study for a business we haven't started yet?</button></p><div id="acFaqCollapse4" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="acFaqHeading4" data-bs-parent="#accordionAdvisoryFaq"><div class="accordion-body">Yes. In fact, that is exactly what a feasibility study is for. We assess the market opportunity, model the financial projections, identify the key risks, and give you an objective view of whether the business is viable - before you commit capital or time to it.</div></div></div>
            <div class="accordion-item"><p class="accordion-header" id="acFaqHeading5"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#acFaqCollapse5" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="acFaqCollapse5">05. How long does a financial assessment or feasibility study take?</button></p><div id="acFaqCollapse5" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="acFaqHeading5" data-bs-parent="#accordionAdvisoryFaq"><div class="accordion-body">Most financial assessments are completed within 1–2 weeks, depending on the complexity of the business and the availability of financial data. Feasibility studies typically take 2–4 weeks. We confirm the timeline during the scoping stage so you can plan around it.</div></div></div>
            <div class="accordion-item"><p class="accordion-header" id="acFaqHeading6"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#acFaqCollapse6" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="acFaqCollapse6">06. Is the budgeting and forecasting service a one-time engagement or ongoing?</button></p><div id="acFaqCollapse6" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="acFaqHeading6" data-bs-parent="#accordionAdvisoryFaq"><div class="accordion-body">Either. Some clients engage us for a one-time annual budget at the start of the financial year. Others prefer an ongoing arrangement where we update the forecast each quarter based on actual performance - turning it into a live management tool rather than a static document.</div></div></div>
            <div class="accordion-item"><p class="accordion-header" id="acFaqHeading7"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#acFaqCollapse7" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="acFaqCollapse7">07. Will CAAFT represent us in investor or board meetings?</button></p><div id="acFaqCollapse7" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="acFaqHeading7" data-bs-parent="#accordionAdvisoryFaq"><div class="accordion-body">Under a virtual CFO engagement, yes - we can participate in investor calls, board meetings, or lender discussions as your financial representative. This is one of the core differences between a CFO engagement and a standard advisory project.</div></div></div>
            <div class="accordion-item"><p class="accordion-header" id="acFaqHeading8"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#acFaqCollapse8" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="acFaqCollapse8">08. Can CAAFT handle a business valuation if our books are not fully up to date?</button></p><div id="acFaqCollapse8" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="acFaqHeading8" data-bs-parent="#accordionAdvisoryFaq"><div class="accordion-body">We can begin the process, but a reliable valuation requires clean, current financials. If your books need to be updated first, our accounting team can bring them current before the valuation begins - ensuring the output is accurate and defensible. We coordinate both internally.</div></div></div>
        </div></div></div></div></div>
